TAILOR

32
00:04:01,500 --> 00:04:04,900
You'll flunk, lazybones

33
00:04:05,200 --> 00:04:08,800
You'll flunk your final exam

34
00:04:09,700 --> 00:04:13,200
You'll see, Leitão, you lazybones

35
00:04:13,600 --> 00:04:16,500
You'll flunk your final exam

36
00:04:17,100 --> 00:04:21,000
You'll see, lazybones
You shall flunk.

37
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:56,200
5th year.
Medical Practice Examination.

38
00:04:56,400 --> 00:05:00,300
Sebastião da Costa Valente.
Valente? (Valiant)

39
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:02,400
That's me.

40
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:08,200
Teófilo das Neves Claro.
Claro? (White)

41
00:05:08,500 --> 00:05:09,500
Here.

42
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:14,000
I'm going to this exam without
a clear thought in my head.

43
00:05:14,200 --> 00:05:16,800
But I see them pretty dark indeed.

44
00:05:17,100 --> 00:05:20,300
May St. Francis Xavier help me.

45
00:05:21,900 --> 00:05:25,000
- Vasco Leitão.
- At your command, General.

46
00:05:25,900 --> 00:05:30,600
- May the gentle St. Francis help me.
- Good Luck, Vasco, my lad.

47
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:36,500
So you're saying that water
in the belly is Pott's Disease

48
00:05:37,300 --> 00:05:40,000
and you advise an injection?!

49
00:05:40,300 --> 00:05:42,500
What?! An injection?

50
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:48,200
Do you know what happens if you stick
a needle in the diaphragm?

51
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:50,600
You shall not touch it!

52
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:55,800
Sorry, but if I stick a needle there,
I assure you I'll touch it.

53
00:05:58,200 --> 00:06:03,100
You just mentioned bicarbonate
for varicose veins.

54
00:06:04,400 --> 00:06:08,800
- By Jove!
- Sorry! But I said benzonaphthol.

55
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:13,200
''Vasco Leitão...

56
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:16,900
...Failed''

57
00:06:29,100 --> 00:06:31,300
''Trás-os-Montes, 20th June,

58
00:06:31,400 --> 00:06:34,800
1933. Tua.''

59
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:38,100
''My Dear Vasco,

60
00:06:38,300 --> 00:06:42,000
''I hope that this letter finds you
in good health.''

61
00:06:42,200 --> 00:06:44,800
You said in your last letter

62
00:06:45,500 --> 00:06:48,400
that you passed your exam
with flying colours,

63
00:06:48,600 --> 00:06:51,200
and that you are now a doctor.

64
00:06:52,100 --> 00:06:56,800
And also that you have set
a superb office.

65
00:06:58,800 --> 00:07:01,500
Let me turn the page, sister, please.

66
00:07:02,800 --> 00:07:07,200
Fortunately, our money
has been put to good use.

67
00:07:08,100 --> 00:07:12,700
As we know you would never deceive
your aunts,

68
00:07:13,400 --> 00:07:17,200
we have decided to go
and celebrate your success,

69
00:07:17,400 --> 00:07:20,900
and also get to know Lisbon,
a city we have never seen.

70
00:07:21,300 --> 00:07:25,300
Sister, please, have a heart,
don't rush me.

71
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:28,400
Now, you were saying...

72
00:07:28,900 --> 00:07:31,200
We can even picture

73
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:35,400
your face lighting up with joy.

74
00:07:35,700 --> 00:07:38,200
''Best regards from us all.

75
00:07:38,400 --> 00:07:42,000
''We shall arrive on Saturday
at 12:40H.

76
00:07:42,700 --> 00:07:47,200
''Your loving aunts,
Efigénia and Perpétua Rocha.''

77
00:07:48,600 --> 00:07:52,800
You scared me, man. Sit down.
What do you think of this?

78
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:55,700
Such a big fib.
And what a mess you're in.

79
00:08:11,400 --> 00:08:12,600
Thank you.

80
00:08:36,800 --> 00:08:39,400
I'm coming, I won't be a moment.

81
00:08:47,900 --> 00:08:49,900
Hello, my pretty flower.

82
00:08:50,100 --> 00:08:53,500
Hello, neighbour.
You look very happy!

83
00:08:53,800 --> 00:08:55,800
Things are going very well for me.

84
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:57,900
- Did you do your exam?
- I did. I got 20.

85
00:08:58,100 --> 00:08:59,100
Congratulations.

86
00:08:59,300 --> 00:09:02,100
I got 20 minutes of cross-examination
as if I were in Prison.

87
00:09:02,300 --> 00:09:03,400
And in the end?

88
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:06,400
Failed. It has upset me so!

89
00:09:06,700 --> 00:09:09,100
You haven't lost any weight over it
though.

90
00:09:09,300 --> 00:09:13,100
Not everyone can be as you are,
Maria da Graça. Such a supple figure.

91
00:09:13,300 --> 00:09:15,900
You're the pin-up
of our neighbourhood.

92
00:09:16,100 --> 00:09:20,800
From now on I shall call you the Greta
Garbo of Castelinhos neighbourhood.

93
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:24,600
How nice!
And what shall I call you?

94
00:09:24,800 --> 00:09:27,400
Call me whatever you want.
Call me something sweet.

95
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:31,400
Call me Bibi or Lulu.

96
00:09:32,400 --> 00:09:33,800
Call me...

97
00:09:34,200 --> 00:09:38,600
Call me whenever you like
and I shall go straight to you.

98
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:41,200
Be serious.

99
00:09:41,800 --> 00:09:45,100
Bye-bye.
Granny's little treasure.

100
00:09:46,200 --> 00:09:48,700
Well, courting the charming singer?

101
00:09:48,900 --> 00:09:53,400
Then you tell me I'm your only love
and that your fate is to be with me.

102
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:55,000
Don't be so mean to me.

103
00:09:55,200 --> 00:09:59,100
Traitor, liar. You think you're
a big lady-killer, don't you?

104
00:09:59,300 --> 00:10:01,700
If what I say isn't true,
let my head be chopped off.

105
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:03,500
I'm stuck.

106
00:10:03,800 --> 00:10:08,300
My father's right, he says you're
a liar, a cheat, a rogue and stuck up.

107
00:10:08,500 --> 00:10:11,800
Stuck up? I wish.
Look where the window is.

108
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:16,900
Lili, don't upset me today.
I'm so sad. I failed my exam.

109
00:10:17,300 --> 00:10:20,200
And on top of that my aunts
from Trás-os-Montes are arriving,

110
00:10:20,300 --> 00:10:22,700
those to whom I've told
I'm already a doctor.

111
00:10:22,800 --> 00:10:25,100
What a fine husband I'll have,
liar and flirtatious.

112
00:10:25,300 --> 00:10:29,600
Me?! Watch your mouth.
You'd better not mention flirts.

113
00:10:29,800 --> 00:10:32,500
- What do you mean by that?
- You flirt with every boy you meet.

114
00:10:32,700 --> 00:10:35,200
- It's a lie! Not with them all!
- It's true.

115
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:38,800
I can even count them. Carlos is one.

116
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:42,600
Ernesto, the chemist's assistant,
that hunchbacked idiot makes it two.

117
00:10:42,800 --> 00:10:46,000
The other one, Julião, makes it 3.

118
00:10:46,200 --> 00:10:49,300
Ten cadets from the military Academy
makes it 13.

119
00:10:49,500 --> 00:10:52,100
With Asdrubal, 14. Julio, 15.

120
00:10:52,300 --> 00:10:55,400
Luís, 16.
Here comes the guillotine!

121
00:10:59,400 --> 00:11:01,900
Mr. Caetano, don't get mad
at the girl.

122
00:11:02,100 --> 00:11:07,000
Let her flirt with whom she pleases.
Let's try the coat, I'm in a hurry.

123
00:11:07,300 --> 00:11:12,200
My apologies. But a father has to
watch over his daughter's happiness.

124
00:11:12,500 --> 00:11:15,100
- But, Daddy...
- Shut up.

125
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:18,500
And don't cry
or you'll rust the pins.

126
00:11:18,700 --> 00:11:21,000
You're embarrassing me
in front of a customer.

127
00:11:21,700 --> 00:11:24,600
Gabriel isn't a customer,
he's a friend.

128
00:11:24,800 --> 00:11:28,600
He's a father himself.
He also has a family ''on his back''.

129
00:11:28,800 --> 00:11:31,200
Look how this fits you in the back.

130
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:34,600
- Yes, but I love him.
- ''I love him, I love him.''

131
00:11:35,200 --> 00:11:39,900
A bohemian who will never settle down.
A cheater who is not fit for you.

132
00:11:40,100 --> 00:11:44,000
- How's this for a fit?
- If you don't approve, I'll elope.

133
00:11:46,900 --> 00:11:50,000
How dare you say that to my face?

134
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:52,800
If I catch that good-for-nothing,

135
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:55,600
I'll grab him by his collar
and finish him up.

136
00:11:55,800 --> 00:11:57,800
Please be careful, Caetano!

137
00:11:58,000 --> 00:12:02,100
You're right.
I'm sorry, Gabriel, I lost my temper.

138
00:12:02,900 --> 00:12:07,800
That buccaneer is deceiving her.
And this buckram isn't good either.

139
00:12:08,200 --> 00:12:11,400
- Students are all penniless riffraff.
- He's not penniless.

140
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:15,000
Vasco has aunts up North who will
leave him everything when they die.

141
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:18,200
What are you saying?
Is it anything worthwhile?

142
00:12:18,300 --> 00:12:23,200
You can't imagine! One has 400,000,
another 100,000 and the other 300,000.

143
00:12:23,400 --> 00:12:25,000
Hold on, hold on, girl!

144
00:12:27,600 --> 00:12:31,600
400, 100 and 300.

145
00:12:34,700 --> 00:12:38,200
- That's 800,000 escudos!
- What about checking this?

146
00:12:38,400 --> 00:12:41,400
I'm checking it right here.

147
00:13:36,400 --> 00:13:39,500
Dearest aunts! My dearest aunts!

148
00:13:40,400 --> 00:13:43,300
Oh, my little boy!
My dearest boy!

149
00:13:43,500 --> 00:13:46,500
So cute! Thank you.
Thank you so much.

150
00:13:46,800 --> 00:13:49,800
- Dearest nephew. My dearest nephew.
- Leave it there.

151
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:53,300
- Give me a hand, do.
- Oh Lord, what an ordeal!

152
00:13:53,500 --> 00:13:57,200
I'm going to fall.
I'm not used to this contraption.

153
00:13:58,000 --> 00:14:00,300
- Here are some flowers.
- Thank you.

154
00:14:00,600 --> 00:14:03,500
- What a joy! What a joy to see you.
- Let's go.

155
00:14:14,400 --> 00:14:16,700
- Oh, my bag!
- And my money!

156
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:19,400
- Oh dear, I feel sick.
- I'm going to faint.

157
00:14:19,600 --> 00:14:23,400
Hey, Vasco! What are you doing there
with those two old maids?

158
00:14:23,700 --> 00:14:27,000
Leave me be. These are my aunts.
They just arrived from up north.

159
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:29,600
Their bags were stolen, they fainted,

160
00:14:29,800 --> 00:14:32,900
I'm flat broke and I can't take them
to a hotel. I don't know what to do.

161
00:14:33,100 --> 00:14:37,100
- We'll take them in the Bullfight Cab.
- Are you crazy?

162
00:14:40,300 --> 00:14:42,900
We drop them at some hotel.
It's cheaper this way.

163
00:14:43,100 --> 00:14:45,600
Are you crazy?
Take them in the Bullfight Cab?!

164
00:14:45,800 --> 00:14:49,500
Don't do this to me, chaps!
This one is going to fall down.

165
00:14:51,600 --> 00:14:56,500
This is outrageous. It's a shame.
Get your hands off the old girls.

166
00:14:58,200 --> 00:15:02,400
Hands off the old girls.
This is outrageous. Why me?!

167
00:15:17,900 --> 00:15:21,500
Hooray for Vasco's aunts!
Hooray!

168
00:15:38,200 --> 00:15:41,000
Keep quiet, lads.
Come on, aunts.

169
00:15:54,800 --> 00:15:58,000
- What is this? What's this?
- It's nothing, aunt.

170
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:11,700
It's a bullfight!
That's a bullfight poster I'm seeing.

171
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:14,800
It's not a bullfight.
It's something else.

172
00:16:16,800 --> 00:16:19,400
Don't get upset, aunt.

173
00:16:20,200 --> 00:16:22,500
This is all your fault.

174
00:16:23,400 --> 00:16:25,900
Stop! Stop this!

175
00:16:26,800 --> 00:16:29,500
Please, stop this!

176
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:37,600
It's going to stop.

177
00:16:37,900 --> 00:16:40,400
I want to get out of here!

178
00:17:07,500 --> 00:17:10,700
Lads, for goodness sake!
This is a family matter.

179
00:17:10,900 --> 00:17:13,900
- Let me explain...
- What do you want to explain? This?

180
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:16,800
There. It's all explained.

181
00:17:50,000 --> 00:17:51,400
- Vasco!
- Alice?

182
00:17:51,800 --> 00:17:54,700
- Your father's out? I'm going in!
- What if he shows up?

183
00:17:54,900 --> 00:17:57,600
- Let me make the most of this moment!
- Give me a kiss.

184
00:17:57,800 --> 00:18:00,600
- People are looking.
- Who? A busybody?

185
00:18:00,800 --> 00:18:02,000
Give me a kiss...

186
00:18:12,300 --> 00:18:15,200
You're sad. Did your aunts arrive?

187
00:18:15,400 --> 00:18:17,800
- Yes! But things aren't going well.
- Why?

188
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:20,500
I'll tell you later.
Now I want a kiss, but a real one.

189
00:18:20,700 --> 00:18:24,200
Let me go. Go kiss your neighbour,
the singer, you rake.

190
00:18:24,400 --> 00:18:27,100
Have you forgotten
what you did to me this morning?

191
00:18:28,400 --> 00:18:30,700
Where can I hide, Alice? Oh, dear!

192
00:18:32,500 --> 00:18:34,800
Watch it, I'll fall.
Where shall I go?

193
00:18:35,200 --> 00:18:37,200
In here?
I might not fit in here.

194
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:41,600
- Quick, quick!
- Don't push me! Don't push me so!

195
00:18:43,300 --> 00:18:46,000
Not under the table.
He'll see me here for sure.

196
00:18:46,200 --> 00:18:48,400
- In here.
- Not in there either.

197
00:18:48,600 --> 00:18:50,500
Why not? Where then?

198
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:55,000
Let's go in, madam. I'm sure
I have something to your taste.

199
00:18:55,200 --> 00:18:58,400
- Please go in.
- I want something very good.

200
00:18:58,600 --> 00:19:01,800
But I will not spend more
than 100 escudos.

201
00:19:02,600 --> 00:19:05,700
Alice, dear! How have you been?

202
00:19:05,900 --> 00:19:07,900
- How are you, madam?
- Well, thank you.

203
00:19:08,200 --> 00:19:09,700
Have a seat, madam.

204
00:19:10,200 --> 00:19:15,000
I always buy winter clothes
in the summer. They're cheaper now.

205
00:19:15,200 --> 00:19:18,500
Quite right. But here in my store,
we have everything:

206
00:19:18,700 --> 00:19:21,400
raincoats, overcoats, cloaks.

207
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:25,500
Now, I even have
a second hand leather coat,

208
00:19:25,700 --> 00:19:28,200
which is superb, a real bargain.

209
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:32,800
- Show me. Maybe I like it.
- You'll see it's an excellent buy.

210
00:19:34,700 --> 00:19:39,400
- This is something special.
- Let me see the lining.

211
00:19:40,800 --> 00:19:42,900
It's as good as new.

212
00:19:44,400 --> 00:19:47,600
Granny, that dummy hit me.

213
00:19:47,800 --> 00:19:50,600
Be quiet, boy, and behave yourself.

214
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:55,400
For you, madam, I'll make you
a special price of 250 escudos.

215
00:19:55,700 --> 00:20:00,400
- I can't afford it, it's too much.
- What a pity. It would be a good buy.

216
00:20:00,600 --> 00:20:04,200
- But it's too expensive.
- Let me see if I have something else.

217
00:20:04,600 --> 00:20:07,500
Something cheaper, much cheaper.

218
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:10,000
What about this one?

219
00:20:10,300 --> 00:20:14,900
- No, no. It's too long for my Jorge.
- Really?!

220
00:20:15,200 --> 00:20:18,700
You will not leave my store
without a good buy.

221
00:20:18,900 --> 00:20:23,800
I hope so, but bargains only.
I can't afford to spend too much.

222
00:20:24,400 --> 00:20:28,000
Who knows if a shepherd's mantle
would please you?

223
00:20:28,500 --> 00:20:30,000
A mouse!

224
00:20:30,400 --> 00:20:33,200
A mouse!! Daddy, a mouse!!

225
00:20:36,300 --> 00:20:38,500
No, a mouse, no!

226
00:20:38,900 --> 00:20:41,000
Please, Daddy, kill the mouse!

227
00:20:41,300 --> 00:20:43,700
Dad, kill it, please.

228
00:20:45,200 --> 00:20:48,200
I'm so scared, so scared!

229
00:20:50,800 --> 00:20:54,700
Such fuss over a mouse.
Lower your skirts. Get off there.

230
00:20:56,000 --> 00:20:59,000
What the deuce!
I don't want any noise in here.

231
00:21:02,900 --> 00:21:07,100
- Oh, you big rascal!
- Daddy, the 800 thousand!

232
00:21:07,300 --> 00:21:11,200
Sorry, Mr. Caetano.
I'll tidy it all up and go right away.

233
00:21:11,400 --> 00:21:12,800
Don't you dare!

234
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:15,300
Get inside. Inside!

235
00:21:21,200 --> 00:21:25,200
How do you dare going right away?
It's a pleasure to have you in here!

236
00:21:25,600 --> 00:21:28,200
My dear doctor, don't worry.
Come, please.

237
00:21:28,400 --> 00:21:31,100
- But I'll tidy it all up.
- Don't worry.

238
00:21:32,400 --> 00:21:34,100
Again?

239
00:21:34,400 --> 00:21:35,900
Get inside.

240
00:21:37,500 --> 00:21:38,900
Go, go.

241
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:42,000
- Thank you.
- Please, doctor.

242
