01:20:55,800 --> 01:20:59,600
it bewitches, fascinates
and captivates.

955
01:20:59,800 --> 01:21:03,200
You'll find it's even great

956
01:21:03,400 --> 01:21:06,200
to hear it on the wireless.

957
01:21:07,300 --> 01:21:09,400
When it is sung with passion,

958
01:21:09,400 --> 01:21:12,400
with tradition and devotion,

959
01:21:12,600 --> 01:21:16,000
our Fado is wonderful
and enthrals us all.

960
01:21:16,300 --> 01:21:20,400
It's our most popular song,
it makes us vibrate with emotion

961
01:21:20,600 --> 01:21:24,300
and that's why
I m a doctor and a Fado singer.

962
01:21:24,800 --> 01:21:26,100
Thank you.

963
01:21:27,400 --> 01:21:29,400
- Very well, doctor!
- Thanks.

964
01:21:32,800 --> 01:21:35,600
So, my friend?!
Here we are!

965
01:21:45,200 --> 01:21:49,000
You see, I was right
in wanting to bring you here.

966
01:21:49,200 --> 01:21:50,900
I'm so touched.

967
01:21:51,100 --> 01:21:54,200
My friend Asdrubal.
You're always so kind, my friend.

968
01:21:54,400 --> 01:21:57,800
I sang as I always do.
Araújo, always here so devotedly.

969
01:21:58,000 --> 01:22:02,600
Dr. Vasco, please accept this token
from a great admirer of yours.

970
01:22:02,800 --> 01:22:06,800
Thank you, miss.
Give me a kiss, you little minx.

971
01:22:07,100 --> 01:22:10,300
Vasco, please, they want more Fado.

972
01:22:10,600 --> 01:22:14,500
- Sing the ''double-pneumonia'' Fado.
- Vasco, dear...

973
01:22:16,300 --> 01:22:20,000
Go away, you cruel Aunts, away!

974
01:22:20,200 --> 01:22:24,000
Now you acknowledge me because
you know I do not need your money.

975
01:22:24,200 --> 01:22:28,800
Thank you. Now, thank God,
I can earn a living.

976
01:22:28,900 --> 01:22:32,400
- I'm no heavy load on anyone.
- Damnation! You're heavy!

977
01:22:32,600 --> 01:22:36,700
I'm sorry, Alexandrino.
Excuse me. Away!

978
01:22:42,200 --> 01:22:47,100
Lads, no more Fado songs.
I sang here today for the last time.

979
01:22:47,400 --> 01:22:52,000
- No more ''Little Anatomy Vasco''.
- No, Vasco, don't do that.

980
01:22:52,300 --> 01:22:54,400
Tomorrow I'll take my exam again,

981
01:22:54,600 --> 01:22:58,500
and I shall be once and for all
Dr. Vasco Leitão.

982
01:22:59,300 --> 01:23:02,400
Farewell,
Fado lovers of my country.

983
01:23:20,100 --> 01:23:21,400
Thank you!

984
01:23:24,700 --> 01:23:26,600
Thank you, my friend.

985
01:23:28,600 --> 01:23:31,100
We shall miss you, man.

986
01:23:31,800 --> 01:23:35,700
Let me through.
You can't stop me, let me through.

987
01:23:42,100 --> 01:23:43,600
Goodbye, Vasco.

988
01:23:44,000 --> 01:23:45,500
Excuse me.

989
01:23:46,200 --> 01:23:49,200
- Goodbye, Vasco.
- It's a real pity.

990
01:23:49,600 --> 01:23:52,400
Let me through, gentleman.
Vasco!

991
01:23:52,700 --> 01:23:54,000
My little Vasco!

992
01:24:26,400 --> 01:24:31,200
What do you know
about parasiticide action?

993
01:24:31,500 --> 01:24:34,000
- And anti-dotal?
- And anti-toxic?

994
01:24:34,200 --> 01:24:37,800
It's a process through which
medications do their healing process.

995
01:24:38,000 --> 01:24:42,500
According to Dr. Mata, pages 129 and
following, in his ''Pharmacology'' book,

996
01:24:42,700 --> 01:24:44,600
third edition, 1921,

997
01:24:44,800 --> 01:24:48,900
printed by the National Press
at Rua Escola Politécnica, 111 to 119,

998
01:24:49,100 --> 01:24:50,900
in Lisbon,

999
01:24:51,200 --> 01:24:53,900
the plastering masses
of vesicant action,

1000
01:24:54,100 --> 01:24:56,200
are nowadays often replaced

1001
01:24:56,400 --> 01:24:59,600
by the tainting-vesicant liquor
of Squyal,

1002
01:24:59,800 --> 01:25:01,900
an ether-aseptic
tincture of Brechten,

1003
01:25:02,100 --> 01:25:05,000
the formula for which can be found
in the British Pharmacopoeia,

1004
01:25:05,200 --> 01:25:08,500
the 1885 edition,
on pages 239 and following.

1005
01:25:08,700 --> 01:25:13,000
In the same case is the vesicatory
liquid of Bidet, F. de Bouchardat,

1006
01:25:13,200 --> 01:25:18,100
1894, on page 435. But it is less
applied than the former one.

1007
01:25:18,600 --> 01:25:21,800
The ordinary extracts are medications
that result from evaporation...

1008
01:25:22,000 --> 01:25:25,400
That's enough. Enough.
I can see that you know.

1009
01:25:25,600 --> 01:25:27,000
What is...?

1010
01:25:27,300 --> 01:25:30,600
- You first, esteemed colleague.
- Please, go ahead.

1011
01:25:31,400 --> 01:25:33,600
One further question.

1012
01:25:34,000 --> 01:25:37,600
Which is the main
lateral-flexor muscle

1013
01:25:38,100 --> 01:25:39,800
of the neck?

1014
01:25:40,000 --> 01:25:43,200
It's the sternocleidomastoid.

1015
01:25:45,300 --> 01:25:49,300
Oh, my dear boy!
He even knows what the mastoid is.

1016
01:25:49,500 --> 01:25:51,000
The mastoid!

1017
01:25:51,200 --> 01:25:54,900
- Madam, what did he say?
- What he said pleased me a lot.

1018
01:25:55,200 --> 01:25:58,400
Listen, João,
what's this mastoid thing?

1019
01:25:58,600 --> 01:26:01,100
You're a Fado singer
and you don't know?

1020
01:26:01,300 --> 01:26:03,200
- No, I don't.
- Neither do I.

1021
01:26:03,300 --> 01:26:07,100
He even knows what the mastoid is!
Imagine that!

1022
01:26:11,200 --> 01:26:13,400
What else can we ask him?

1023
01:26:15,700 --> 01:26:17,400
Is that you, Alice?

1024
01:26:17,700 --> 01:26:21,600
Everything is fine. Imagine!
He even knows what the mastoid is.

1025
01:26:21,800 --> 01:26:25,200
Oh, bliss!
Thank you, Daddy, see you later.

1026
01:26:25,700 --> 01:26:28,600
The mastoid! My darling Vasco!

1027
01:26:29,500 --> 01:26:31,900
But what is this mastoid thing?

1028
01:26:32,200 --> 01:26:34,400
We are satisfied.

1029
01:26:35,800 --> 01:26:38,700
- Very good, Vasco.
- Very good.

1030
01:26:52,700 --> 01:26:57,100
I've been deaf for 20 years
and I never heard an exam like this.

1031
01:26:58,000 --> 01:27:01,600
Doctor, if you want,
I'll give you 300 escudos

1032
01:27:01,800 --> 01:27:05,200
if you sing the ''mastoid'' Fado
at my place this Sunday.

1033
01:27:05,500 --> 01:27:08,600
- I can't, my friend.
- Accept it, Doc.

1034
01:27:11,200 --> 01:27:13,400
You left the professors speechless.

1035
01:27:16,800 --> 01:27:18,800
Give him a hug.

1036
01:27:21,000 --> 01:27:23,400
What a touching scene.

1037
01:27:26,800 --> 01:27:29,800
- The aunts.
- The aunts. Let them come hither.

1038
01:27:30,000 --> 01:27:31,900
Let the family through.

1039
01:27:35,400 --> 01:27:38,500
I can't forget the mastoid!

1040
01:27:39,000 --> 01:27:41,900
- Don't cry, ladies, don't.
- I can't help it.

1041
01:27:42,100 --> 01:27:44,900
- It was a fine exam!
- As fine as his heart.

1042
01:27:45,100 --> 01:27:47,600
- Thank you.
- Hooray for Vasco!

1043
01:28:09,600 --> 01:28:11,100
I request the floor!

1044
01:28:16,000 --> 01:28:19,800
- Do you like to feel my hand?
- I do!

1045
01:28:20,000 --> 01:28:21,700
- Why?
- I don't know.

1046
01:28:23,500 --> 01:28:25,400
I request the floor!

1047
01:28:25,800 --> 01:28:28,200
Dammit! I request the floor!

1048
01:28:34,800 --> 01:28:37,200
- I'm no speaker.
- Hear, hear.

1049
01:28:38,500 --> 01:28:40,800
The only speech I've ever made

1050
01:28:41,100 --> 01:28:44,200
was by the cold tomb
of my friend Ernesto,

1051
01:28:44,600 --> 01:28:46,700
who died in his prime.

1052
01:28:48,100 --> 01:28:49,800
And it was made...

1053
01:28:50,800 --> 01:28:52,900
...between hiccups...

1054
01:28:53,300 --> 01:28:55,600
...that I said goodbye
to a great friend,

1055
01:28:55,800 --> 01:28:59,400
with no disregard for Vasco there,
who is also a great friend.

1056
01:28:59,900 --> 01:29:00,900
Hear, hear.

1057
01:29:01,200 --> 01:29:04,100
- I have no oratory gifts.
- Hear, hear.

1058
01:29:04,300 --> 01:29:07,800
I have no words,
I have no wine either.

1059
01:29:08,900 --> 01:29:13,800
- But I have something inside...
- Couldn't that be air in your pipes?

1060
01:29:15,800 --> 01:29:19,800
What I feel inside me
can only be ''sastifaction''

1061
01:29:20,000 --> 01:29:23,100
for this auspicious marriage
celebrated today,

1062
01:29:23,300 --> 01:29:26,700
and that I wish
there will be many more to come.

1063
01:29:32,800 --> 01:29:36,100
Vasco, Vasco, Vasco!

1064
01:29:38,600 --> 01:29:40,800
Speech, Vasco!

1065
01:29:43,100 --> 01:29:45,200
I request the floor.

1066
01:29:48,900 --> 01:29:52,000
Ladies,
so lovely and charming,

1067
01:29:52,200 --> 01:29:55,800
for your grace and charm
I thank you kindly.

1068
01:29:56,300 --> 01:29:59,300
Gentlemen,
if you're ailing and ill

1069
01:29:59,600 --> 01:30:03,200
or with pneumonia afflicted
treat you I sure will.

1070
01:30:03,600 --> 01:30:06,600
Lisbon now has in me a doctor,

1071
01:30:06,800 --> 01:30:10,400
besides physician,
you see, I'm an inventor.

1072
01:30:11,200 --> 01:30:14,300
I'll be there ready to see you,
to vaccinate and cure you,

1073
01:30:14,500 --> 01:30:18,600
to cut you and sew you up again
and smilingly mitigate your pain.

1074
01:30:18,900 --> 01:30:22,100
My satisfaction,
worth and dedication

1075
01:30:22,300 --> 01:30:26,100
are in this invention:
the Happy Therapy medication.

1076
01:30:26,400 --> 01:30:29,400
To handle an emergency,
I can now guarantee,

1077
01:30:29,600 --> 01:30:33,400
but from a contingency
should you die, die laughingly.

1078
01:30:36,000 --> 01:30:39,600
The End

1079
01:30:42,700 --> 01:30:47,400
Translation: Maria Gabriel
Subtitling: CRISTBET, LDA.